Wrapping up a busy week in DC! I’m proud to say that among the items passed this week in the House was an amendment I authored to allocate $4 million from the Department of Defense to Historically Black Colleges and Universities. #hbcu

In honor of #TeacherAppreciationDay I want to say thank you to all the teachers in America and our great Hoosier state your hard work and dedication doesn't go unnoticed. All of us are who we are because of you. #TeacherAppreciationWeek

Today is #ElectionDay! Make sure you go out today and cast your vote. Remember EVERY vote counts! Polls are open from 6AM-6PM. Go to https://t.co/CEh89Wwver to find your polling location. #Election2019

Today is #EqualPayDay. We still have to keep working in order to close the existing #genderpaygap. With the Paycheck Fairness Act we hope that soon women's salaries will be based on their experience and accomplishments and not their gender. #EqualPayDay2019

Two years ago today President Trump initiated his second immigration directive to implement a travel ban. Today we are still fighting to reverse it. These immigrants and refugees deserve the same safety and opportunity as others applying for asylum. #travelban #immigrantrights
